# Engineering Rules

- Prefer standard Angular and TypeScript tooling, project structure, and build/test conventions over custom infrastructure.
- Keep Gherkin specifications, automated tests, and Angular implementation aligned so behavior remains traceable from feature text to working code.
- Preserve clear boundaries between UI components, services, routing, state, and API integration.
- Keep user-facing behavior accessible, responsive, and consistent with the approved Gherkin scenarios.
- Verify changes with focused Angular and TypeScript tests, linting, or builds appropriate to the change.
- Before relying on external tools or libraries such as `ng`, `npm`, testing frameworks, or browser APIs, verify their invocation contract from primary documentation or local help output.
